MoSP core and sim_viewer can be used with virtualenv, example:

 * setup virtualenv
   wget https://raw.github.com/pypa/virtualenv/master/virtualenv.py
   python2.7 virtualenv.py --no-site-packages mosp-py2.7-simpy2.3
 * activate virtualenv
   cd mosp-py2.7-simpy2.3
   source bin/activate
 * install SimPy
   pip install http://dfn.dl.sourceforge.net/project/simpy/simpy/SimPy-2.3/SimPy-2.3.tar.gz
 * install pyglet for sim_viewer
   pip install pyglet
 * install MoSP
   git clone https://github.com/bhenne/MoSP.git mosp
   # or: wget https://github.com/bhenne/MoSP/zipball/master; unzip master; rm master 

